Wash and dry all produce. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Quarter @lime{1}. Trim and quarter @cremini mushrooms{4%ounce}. Halve, peel, and cut @yellow onion{1}(half diced). Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger; cook, stirring, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together half the @cornstarch{1/2%tablespoon} and 1/4 cup cold water until smooth.

Whisk in @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, half the @Szechuan paste{2%tablespoon}, juice from half the lime, and @sugar{1%teaspoon}.

> For 4 servings, use all the cornstarch and 1/3 cup cold water, all the Szechuan paste, juice from whole lime, and 2 tsp sugar.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, diced onion, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and lightly charred, ~{5-7%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}.

Add broccoli, a splash of water, salt, and pepper to pan; cover and steam for ~{3%minutes}.

Uncover and add a large drizzle of oil. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and lightly charred, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

Transfer to plate with mushrooms and onion.

Add another drizzle of oil to pan. Add garlic; cook, stirring, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in sauce. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in veggies, @cashews{1/2%ounce}, and @butter{1%tablespoon} until coated. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> Stir in a splash more water if your sauce is too thick.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #plates{} and top with stir-fry. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.